      • parseVariableIndex

        public static java.lang.Integer parseVariableIndex​(java.lang.String indexedStr,
                                                   java.lang.String semanticLetter,
                                                   java.lang.String varName,
                                                   java.lang.String tabColumn,
                                                   DecorationTableParsingResult res)
        Gets the index of the indexed function parameter. 0 if the right side of the operation is empty. Positive and negative indexes are possible.
        Parameters:
        indexedStr - The string index representation of the indexed function parameter
        semanticLetter - The semantic letter corresponding to this instruction
        varName - The variable name concerned by this indexed function parameter
        tabColumn - The concerned column in the decoration table (Register, Return, Update or Guard).
        res - The DecorationTableParsingResult parsing result (modified by process)
        Returns:
        The indexed function parameter value
